## How many wards sang new hymns each week?

The following plot show what percentage of wards sang from each of the new batches of hymns, per week, since June 2024 when the new hymns started getting rolled out. I've included data from all three batches just so you can compare them to each other.









::: {.cell .column-page}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-7-1.png){width=1344}
:::
:::





Since it's only been one week, there's not a lot to say, almost nobody sang from the fourth batch. In fairness, it was Father's Day in the United States, so people likely had other plans. 

Here's another version of the same plot but instead of the actual dates, it's in terms of how many weeks since the batches came out. We can use this plot to spot any parallel trends across the batches, especially in the first few weeks of their release.



::: {.cell .column-page}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-9-1.png){width=1344}
:::
:::



Here we can see that each batch is a little less popular than the previous one, both overall and week by week. Nearly 20% of wards sang from the first batch the week it came out. About 8% did for the second batch. About 1% for the third batch. And of the 576 wards I have data from on June 15th, just one of them sang from the fourth batch. 








